title: For Sale:  Ruger Mini 14 NIB with EXTRAS!!!!!
postcontent:
Safe queen Mini. Comes with 5 extra mags, installed flash suppressor, and ATI Strikeforce tactical stock. All items are unused and new in the box.

NOTE 4/17/2013: I just received an email from a gentleman accusing me of running a scam because I increased the price of my listing. If anyone is concerned with this being a scam send me an email with your phone number and I will call you to discuss. What is very frustrating about selling something is that people expect you to give something away. Here is a simple breakdown to illustrate my point:

Mini 14 - $849.99 (on sale at Cabelas)
magazines - $161.65 (Buds Gun Shop)
muzzle Brake - $70.00 (sorry but I bought on Ebay so I can't locate the reseller)
ATI Strikeforce - $131.99 (again bought on Ebay)

Lets do the math: 849.99+161.65+70.00+131.99=$1213.63 (mmm $1000 seems to be a fair price)

I actually bought at GAT so I paid $895 (before tax) for the rifle and $199.95 (before tax) for the mags so I have $1296.94 into the gun which I am still selling at a LOSS for $1000 because I feel its a more fair price in light of today's market.

If you can get a better price elsewhere than I encourage you to go there and purchase it. Please refrain from sending me emails complaining or accusing me of things that are untrue. If you are so hell bent on voicing your opinion send me your number and let have a phone discussion like real men do.

This design of SAA was built from 1896 to 1908. The revolver we listed was completely refurbished approximately 12 years ago. title: For Sale:  SPAS 12
location: Saunemin, IL 61769 (near Pontiac, IL), Illinois, United States
postcontent:
Very nice and very rare SPAS 12 for sale. 

The Franchi SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun manufactured by Italian firearms company Franchi from 1979 to 2000. Only five percent (about 1,850) of the estimated SPAS-12 shotguns manufactured were imported into the United States. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 has been sold to military and police users worldwide, on the civilian market, and has been featured in many Movies, TV Shows and Video Games.

The appearance and intended purpose of the SPAS-12 initially led to its "Military" designation. The SPAS-12 was designed from the ground up as a rugged military shotgun and it was named the (Special Purpose Automatic Shotgun). In 1990 Franchi renamed the shotgun to (Sporting Purpose Automatic Shotgun), this allowed continued sales to the U.S. as a limited-magazine-capacity, fixed-stock model until 1994. Following the United States Federal Assault Weapons Ban, imports of SPAS-12 shotguns were stopped to the United States. In September 2004 the ban had expired, but Franchi had ended production in 2000 of the SPAS-12.

As used by Arnold Schwarzenegger in the Terminator movie.
